process

kill pid
if failed, use kill -9 pid, which means forcibly

killall command_name
kill all the processes of the command


job

run in the background:
unzip file.zip &

watch all the jobs:
jobs

switch to the background job by its job number:
%1
fg %1

exit the current running job, turn to sleeping:
Ctrl+z

restart the background job in the background:
%1 &
bg %1

turn the last background job to the foreground:
fg
